Model Name
Sonos Sub Mini - Black
  • Unlock your entertainment when you pair Sub Mini with Beam or Ray and experience dramatic depth that puts you inside your shows, movies, and games.
  • Within the acoustically sealed cabinet, dual custom woofers generate the full-toned low frequencies of a much larger subwoofer. Advanced processing further enhances the bass response.
  • Both woofers face inward to create a force-canceling effect that neutralizes distortion.
  • Trueplay tuning technology adapts the bass for your room's acoustics so it won't sound harsh, muddy, or flat—even if you place Sub Mini next to the wall. Supported iOS device required.

    Customers say

    Customers praise the subwoofer's sound quality, noting it fills rooms without being loud, and appreciate its compact design that works well in smaller rooms. The product receives positive feedback for its value, ease of setup with seamless integration into existing Sonos systems, and top-quality craftsmanship. The functionality and connectivity aspects receive mixed reviews - while the subwoofer works well with Sonos Arc, some customers report issues with the Sonos app, and several mention problems with network connectivity.

      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Massive Sound, Small(er) Package
      Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2025
      Size: SingleColor: Black
      The Sonos Sub Mini produces massive house shaking bass for a deceivingly small package. I use several Sonos speakers throughout my home, including Play:1, beams, Five, and a standard Sub. This Sub Mini is the perfect bass companion to turn any Sonos speaker system into an... See more
      The Sonos Sub Mini produces massive house shaking bass for a deceivingly small package. I use several Sonos speakers throughout my home, including Play:1, beams, Five, and a standard Sub. This Sub Mini is the perfect bass companion to turn any Sonos speaker system into an explosive, rich sound environment.

      It looks great, and is compact enough to make it portable or tuck away under a small end table. Its solid exterior makes it durable and weighty, with a quality feel you would expect from Sonos. It is also simple to connect and add to your existing system, as well as configure for the right amount of bass you want.

      Where the Sub Mini really shines is its powerful output and clear, deep notes, at a price point much lower than the relatively expensive regular Sonos Sub. Having owned a larger Sonos Sub for years, its audio output is astounding, but the Sub Mini rivals the bass output of its big brother very closely. At a price roughly 60% of the Sub, the Sub Mini outputs very similar levels of bass (detectable to my ear from different rooms).

      If you have Sonos speakers and have been considering bumping your audio experience with a subwoofer, I would definitely recommend the Sub Mini. At the price point, you will save much less than a full Sub but get just about all of the room shaking bass.

      I recently purchased the “Sub Mini” to complete my home theater system (Arc, surround speakers, and now the Sub Mini). I want to thank Sonos for producing such a great product, however, installing the Sub Mini was a horrible and frustrating experience. This is not what I expected from Sonos. All of the products that I have purchased were easy and seamless to install. That is why I purchased the Sub Mini, thinking that it too would also be easy to install. NOT SO. The problem was the PIN number that was required. The instructions were clear enough. However, the location of the PIN number and the Font Size and coloring made it almost impossible to read. I am 78 years old and even with my glasses on I could not read the number. It is located on the bottom side of the unit, on the side wall of the indentation where the power cord plugs in. Why would they hide it in such an obscure place. On top of that, it is printed in a light grey color on a black background with almost no contrast and a Font Size that is so small that you can't see it. Would you believe I had to ask my neighbor to read the number for me? I just can’t understand the reasoning behind the location and size of the number. Why not just print it on the underside of the box lid or on a card with the power cord. To say the least, I was frustrated and upset that I couldn't install the sub by myself. Add this problem to their very poor rollout of the updated app, and now I am wondering if I should consider buying any more Sonos products. Sonos needs to fix this issue soon, or risk other poor reviews and lost sales to those of us that aren’t 25 years old. Just be aware that if you purchase one of these, you will need 20/20 vision and a very strong flashlight in order to install it. Once you get it installed, the sound is amazing.

      ☆ Key Features
      - Compact cylindrical design** with force-cancelling six-inch drivers
      - Frequency range down to 25Hz**
      - Wireless connectivity** over Wi-Fi (5GHz) with Ethernet port option
      - Compatible with Sonos Ray, Beam, and Arc soundbars

      ☆ Performance
      The Sub Mini delivers rich, controlled bass that seamlessly integrates with Sonos soundbars. While subtle out of the box, it significantly improves audio depth when adjusted in the Sonos app. Users should increase the sub level to +4 or +5 for optimal performance.

      ☆ Compatibility and Value
      - Best for Sonos Five pair : Highly recommended.
      - Good for Sonos Beam: Solid addition, especially in limited spaces
      - Less recommended for Sonos Ray: Harder to justify the price.

      - Performs well for both movies and music.

      - Relatively expensive
      - Limited to one unit per room
